{ We already mentioned the idea in the notes to 9... Nb4!. We control d5 and open the diagonal a5-d8 for our queen.   In some cases, we might play ...Qb6+ and unpin with a gain of tempo. }
13. Kh1
{ White is expecting ...Qb6 and plays a prophylactic move to address this idea. }
13... Qd6
{ Black has several Queen moves to unpin. We like this one best, as the Queen still covers crucial spots like e5 and f6.   The position offers chances for both sides. We enjoy the Bishop-pair and can put more pressure on the weak d3-pawn by moving a Rook to d8. White can try to utilize the f-file and launch an attack on our King with ideas such as Qe1-h4.   Let's have a look at what happens if White starts this Queen manoeuvre right away. }
