{ According to our plan, we develop our Knight to c6 to prepare ...e5.   We'll check four moves now for White. We'll take a look at the harmless move  8.d5?!  and the main moves  8.Qd2  ,  8.h3  , and  8.Re1  .  Against these moves, we recommend playing  8...b5  , so we have a common approach against all of them.   In the case of  8.Qd2  and  8.Re1  Black has the reasonable alternative  8...Bg4  , fighting for the dark squares by taking on f3. This is a possible way to vary your play. }
