8. Bg5
{ This move was played in a well-known and historically important game.  In the final round of the Candidates Tournament 2013 Vladimir Kramnik had the Black pieces versus the unpredictable Vassily Ivanchuk. Kramnik was sharing first place with Magnus Carlsen before this final round but had the worse tiebreak. He needed to win the game or at least keep winning chances to fight for first place and the all-important qualification for the title match.  Kramnik went for @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.d4  d6  and after  2.e4  the Pirc was on the board, a great opening to stir up a fight. Kramnik opening result was fine, but in the end, he lost the game, Carlsen won the tournament and was crowned World Champion a few months later. }
