{ The position offers chances for both players.   We are very flexible and have many options for how to develop further. Moves like ...Bb7, ...e6 or ...e5 all come to mind. This kind of flexibility is a huge upside of the Pirc.   The central structure is not defined early on; therefore, many different formations are possible. White's setup is sound but not very aggressive. This allows some creativity. }
